dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2010  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4 \"α-Bungarotoxin (α-Bgtx) labeling of nAChR α9 and α10 in cochlear tissues and cultured cells\"\nAt P10 VAChT labeled presynaptic terminals overlap extensively with alpha-Bgtx staining. In cochlear hair cells the alphya-Btx staining is mediated by alpha9/alpha10 heteromeric nAHCRs.\n\nRapsyn, a component of the muscle postsynaptic specialization, binds and mediates aggregation of alpha-Bgtx (=alpha9/alpha10 heteromeric nAHCRs) in non-neuronal cells. This is another indirect indication of localization of alpha9/alpha10 heteromeric nAHCRs to the cholinergic postsynaptic specialization.\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"...we first investigated α-Bgtx labeling of nAChRs in freshly isolated cochlear hair cells from postnatal day P1 and P10 rat pups. \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2010" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

